WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.080
Claude can reason about a contract, but chat alone cannot reliably inspect several Word drafts or create precise tracked changes.

00:08.860 --> 00:14.180
An MCP server gives Claude specialized tools for that work. Claude still does the reasoning.

00:14.860 --> 00:19.180
The server performs the document work and returns results we can check against the source.

00:19.720 --> 00:30.740
Veqtor is an open-source MCP server for Word contract negotiations. It reads redlines, verifies quotations, and creates new drafts with real tracked changes.

00:32.700 --> 00:45.160
In this demo, I ask what happened to the liability cap across four rounds. Veqtor extracts the tracked revisions. Claude turns the evidence into a clear explanation of how the cap and its carve-outs changed.

00:48.040 --> 01:00.200
Then I ask for the counterparty's exact latest wording. Instead of relying on the summary, Veqtor checks the quotation against the source file, character for character, and returns the verified text.

01:05.080 --> 01:16.700
Finally, I turn the review into an action: restore our 150% cap and the willful misconduct carve-out in a new round-five draft. The original stays untouched.

01:18.680 --> 01:27.620
Veqtor checks every edit before writing, then re-checks the saved file. In this run, no unintended changes. That is MCP in practice.

01:27.620 --> 01:37.080
Claude does the reasoning. Veqtor does document work you can verify. It's free, open source, and installs with one command. You're welcome to try it.
